SECURITY NOTES
internal use only

— Violence draws patterns.
— Patterns draw attention.
— Attention escalates.

Reminder:
We do not react emotionally.
We react proportionally.

The recent access violation confirms:
Street-level groups act without foresight.
They confuse fear with leverage.

Leverage requires distance.

Note:
Information is more valuable than force.
Force is loud.
Information is quiet.

External entities should be observed, not confronted.
Observation creates options.

Options create control.

Do not attempt to "solve" unknown groups.
Unknown groups solve themselves
once pressure is applied correctly.

Security is not the absence of threats.
Security is knowing where they are.

End of notes.